vehicle

Class RegularManualTransmission

  • java.lang.Object
    • vehicle.RegularManualTransmission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ManualTransmission 

    public class RegularManualTransmission
extends java.lang.Object
implements ManualTransmission
    This class represents a regular manual transmission vehicle which is an implementation of the manual transmission interface. Regular Manual transmission allows for a speed change of 1 unit at a time and has 5 gears.

        Constructs a Regular Manual Transmission Object ,initializes the highest speed of the vehicle and the five gears based on the different values passed.
        Parameters:
        low1 - the lowest speed for the first Gear.
        high1 - the highest speed for the first Gear.
        low2 - the lowest speed for the second Gear.
        high2 - the highest speed for the second Gear.
        low3 - the lowest speed for the third Gear.
        high3 - the highest speed for the third Gear.
        low4 - the lowest speed for the fourth Gear.
        high4 - the highest speed for the fourth Gear.
        low5 - the lowest speed for the fifth Gear.
        high5 - the highest speed for the fifth Gear and the vehicle itself.
